  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Components are the building blocks of your application. They allow you to create reusable pieces of UI that can be composed together.
  </p>

  <h2 id="creating-components">Creating Components</h2>
  <p>Components are created as <code>.astro</code> files in the <code>src/components</code> directory:</p>
  <pre><code>// src/components/Button.astro
---
interface Props &#123;
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
&#125;

const &#123; variant = 'primary' &#125; = Astro.props;
---

&lt;button class=&#123;`btn btn-$&#123;variant&#125;`&#125;&gt;
  &lt;slot /&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>

  <h2 id="component-props">Component Props</h2>
  <p>Pass data to components using props:</p>
  <pre><code>// Define props with TypeScript
---
interface Props &#123;
  title: string;
  count?: number;
  items: string[];
&#125;

const &#123; title, count = 0, items &#125; = Astro.props;
---

&lt;div&gt;
  &lt;h2&gt;&#123;title&#125;&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Count: &#123;count&#125;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;ul&gt;
    &#123;items.map(item =&gt; &lt;li&gt;&#123;item&#125;&lt;/li&gt;)&#125;
  &lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>Use the component:</p>
  <pre><code>&lt;MyComponent
  title="Hello"
  count=&#123;5&#125;
  items=&#123;['a', 'b', 'c']&#125;
/&gt;</code></pre>

  <h2 id="slots">Slots</h2>
  <p>Slots allow you to pass child content to components:</p>
  <pre><code>// Card.astro
---
interface Props &#123;
  title: string;
&#125;

const &#123; title &#125; = Astro.props;
---

&lt;div class="card"&gt;
  &lt;h3&gt;&#123;title&#125;&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;div class="card-body"&gt;
    &lt;slot /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="card-footer"&gt;
    &lt;slot name="footer" /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>Named slots allow multiple content areas:</p>
  <pre><code>&lt;Card title="My Card"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;This goes in the default slot&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;div slot="footer"&gt;
    &lt;button&gt;Action&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/Card&gt;</code></pre>

  <h2 id="styling">Styling Components</h2>
  <p>Styles in components are scoped by default:</p>
  <pre><code>&lt;div class="container"&gt;
  &lt;slot /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;style&gt;
  /* These styles only apply to this component */
  .container &#123;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1rem;
  &#125;
&lt;/style&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>Use <code>is:global</code> for global styles:</p>
  <pre><code>&lt;style is:global&gt;
  /* These styles apply globally */
  body &#123;
    font-family: system-ui;
  &#125;
&lt;/style&gt;</code></pre>

  <h2 id="client-side">Client-Side Interactivity</h2>
  <p>Add interactivity with client-side scripts:</p>
  <pre><code>&lt;button id="counter"&gt;Count: 0&lt;/button&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
  let count = 0;
  const button = document.getElementById('counter');

  button?.addEventListener('click', () =&gt; &#123;
    count++;
    button.textContent = `Count: $&#123;count&#125;`;
  &#125;);
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

  <blockquote>
    For complex interactivity, consider using framework components (React, Vue, Svelte) with client directives.
  </blockquote>
